    "profile": "American indie pop singer and songwriter known for her 1980s synth-pop and early 2000s pop-inspired music, as well her camp and drag queen–influenced aesthetic. Born Kayleigh Rose Amstutz in Willard, Missouri, on February 19, 1998. Her stage name, Chappell Roan, is a combination of the name of her grandfather, Dennis K. Chappell, who died of brain cancer, and a word taken from his favorite song, \"The Strawberry Roan\" by [a1791599]. ",
